WEBVTT

01:45.770 --> 01:47.290
It's almost new.

01:50.040 --> 01:51.800
Three hundred cartridges.

01:55.640 --> 01:57.640
The guy who
gave it to me said...

01:57.750 --> 02:03.150
you can hit
as far as three kilometers.

02:10.090 --> 02:11.790
How much are you asking
for all of this?

02:12.160 --> 02:13.820
One thousand dirhams.

02:14.200 --> 02:15.860
One thousand dirhams?

02:20.000 --> 02:22.160
I'll give you five hundred.

02:26.910 --> 02:28.030
And a goat.

02:37.150 --> 02:42.490
With this rifle, your sons
will kill plenty of jackals.

02:47.960 --> 02:50.160
Here, let one of your boys try.

02:50.370 --> 02:51.630
Let Yussef shoot.

02:52.170 --> 02:53.500
Dad, I want to shoot first.

03:02.380 --> 03:05.780
This is the safety.
Push it in when you're ready.

03:09.850 --> 03:13.620
If he doesn't hit the jackals,
at least he'll scare the shit out of them.

03:13.860 --> 03:15.190
Your turn Yussef.

03:28.870 --> 03:31.460
He shoots better than you.

03:39.750 --> 03:41.050
Good luck,
have a good day.

03:41.150 --> 03:42.140
God bless you.

03:42.250 --> 03:45.220
Kill at least three jackals.

03:46.090 --> 03:50.580
Make sure no one
sees you with the rifle...

03:50.690 --> 03:54.560
if you see someone coming, hide it.

04:33.600 --> 04:34.800
What are you doing?

04:37.310 --> 04:38.830
I told you,
don't spy on her.

04:38.940 --> 04:40.500
What do you care?

04:40.610 --> 04:42.270
Move it.

05:03.630 --> 05:05.360
Five to two.

05:07.370 --> 05:08.600
There's a jackal.

05:08.700 --> 05:09.670
Where?

05:10.510 --> 05:11.490
Over there.

05:16.340 --> 05:18.710
What are you doing,
you idiot?

05:37.500 --> 05:39.330
Zohra doesn't mind.

05:40.000 --> 05:42.660
She doesn't, but I do.

05:44.510 --> 05:47.480
This is between her and me.

05:48.880 --> 05:53.840
You're both pigs.
Next time I'm going to tell Dad.

05:54.280 --> 05:55.840
Stay out of this.

05:55.950 --> 05:59.480
If you want me to stay out of it,
don't do it.

07:00.080 --> 07:01.240
What are you doing?

07:03.690 --> 07:06.480
Hassan said this bullet
could reach three kilometers.

07:07.090 --> 07:08.990
That rock didn't move.

07:09.090 --> 07:11.490
You don't know how to shoot.
Give me the rifle.

07:19.970 --> 07:20.960
See.

07:21.070 --> 07:23.800
Yeah, but that's not
three kilometers.

07:36.950 --> 07:39.440
I bet the bullet
can't hit that far.

07:43.490 --> 07:45.290
These bullets are lame.

07:46.160 --> 07:47.820
You're not aiming right.

07:51.200 --> 07:53.600
What'll you give me
if I hit that car?

07:54.770 --> 07:56.130
I'll shoot.

08:02.310 --> 08:04.280
You see? Nothing.

08:04.410 --> 08:05.670
Let me shoot.

08:08.020 --> 08:09.570
Shoot at it.

08:24.500 --> 08:26.690
See... nothing.

08:28.670 --> 08:30.230
You're right, they're useless.

08:52.560 --> 08:55.460
Where are these kids?

08:55.730 --> 08:58.260
Where are you?

08:58.870 --> 09:01.330
I'm coming to get you...

09:01.440 --> 09:02.730
Base!

09:04.570 --> 09:06.560
You win.

09:06.970 --> 09:08.670
<i>- Yes?
- Amelia?</i>

09:09.010 --> 09:10.140
Yes, sir.

09:11.180 --> 09:12.270
<i>Hi. How's everything?</i>

09:12.380 --> 09:14.350
Everything is okay, sir.

09:14.820 --> 09:18.450
Mrs. Rachel told me.
I am very sorry, sir.

09:18.820 --> 09:20.380
How's Mrs. Susan?

09:20.560 --> 09:24.490
<i>She's better now.
They're going to have to operate, but...</i>

09:24.830 --> 09:27.320
<i>Look, Rachel's flying in tonight.</i>

09:27.460 --> 09:30.520
<i>She's gonna find someone to
take care of the kids so you can go.</i>

09:30.630 --> 09:34.120
Thank you, sir. Thank you.
I really appreciate it.

09:34.840 --> 09:36.900
<i>So, look after them, okay?
Don't tell them anything.</i>

09:37.000 --> 09:39.500
No, no, no. Don't worry, sir.
Don't worry. Okay.

09:39.610 --> 09:41.630
<i>- Put Mike on, please.
- Yes, sir.</i>

09:41.980 --> 09:44.210
Mike? Your dad is calling.

09:47.950 --> 09:50.510
<i>- Hi, Daddy.
- Hi, sweetie. How are you?</i>

09:50.620 --> 09:54.490
Good. Dad, guess what? Today
they brought hermit crabs to class.

09:54.590 --> 09:55.720
<i>Oh, really?</i>

09:56.420 --> 10:01.090
I held one in my hands. It bit me.
It really didn't bleed, but...

10:01.900 --> 10:04.060
Dad? Are you okay?

10:04.230 --> 10:06.100
<i>I'm okay. Everything's fine.</i>

10:06.200 --> 10:09.000
Mariana wanted to take one home.
But the teacher didn't let her. She was...

10:09.140 --> 10:10.930
I don't want to go to sleep.
I don't want to go to sleep.

10:11.040 --> 10:12.970
Mike. Mike.

10:13.640 --> 10:15.370
Did you brush your teeth?

10:26.290 --> 10:28.450
Sleep with angels, my darling.

10:30.760 --> 10:32.490
Sleep well, sweetie.

10:39.870 --> 10:41.230
Amelia?

10:44.240 --> 10:45.600
Amelia?

10:50.080 --> 10:51.740
Could you leave the light on?

10:51.850 --> 10:53.610
You are already sharing a room...

10:53.710 --> 10:56.910
didn't we agree
to sleep with the lights off?

10:57.020 --> 10:58.320
But I'm scared.

10:58.450 --> 11:00.440
There's nothing to be scared of.

11:00.590 --> 11:04.580
But I'm scared that what happened
to Sam is going to happen to me.

11:06.330 --> 11:10.020
No, that won't happen to you.

11:11.130 --> 11:13.160
Sam died while he was sleeping.

11:13.270 --> 11:15.000
No, baby, no, no.

11:15.370 --> 11:19.830
That only happens to some babies
when they're really, really little.

11:20.610 --> 11:23.740
Your brother is already
high in heaven, baby.

11:24.850 --> 11:28.870
I'll sit here with you.
But you can't talk anymore, okay?

11:29.550 --> 11:30.950
Go to sleep.

12:01.850 --> 12:04.220
But today is my son's wedding, sir.

12:04.320 --> 12:06.080
<i>Cancel your son's wedding.
I'll pay for another one,</i>

12:06.190 --> 12:09.380
<i>I'll pay for a better one.
I need you to do this, Amelia.</i>

12:09.490 --> 12:11.480
Everything is ready, sir.

12:12.360 --> 12:15.920
Can't anyone come to take care
of the kids? It's just one day, sir.

12:16.030 --> 12:17.220
<i>How do you expect me to find someone
from here?</i>

12:17.330 --> 12:20.320
<i>Susan's still recovering, and Rachel
can't make it to take care of the kids.</i>

12:20.430 --> 12:22.160
<i>Can't do it. Hold on.</i>

12:24.010 --> 12:27.570
<i>We're really counting on you, Amelia.
I'm sorry, but you have to do this.</i>

12:27.680 --> 12:29.270
<i>- But...
- Goodbye.</i>

12:38.820 --> 12:41.620
How can I be
in two places at once?

12:41.790 --> 12:44.620
I'm just asking you
to take them for today.

12:45.490 --> 12:48.220
I can't, the mister is still home.

12:48.400 --> 12:49.890
And they aren't going out?

12:50.000 --> 12:51.970
No, I don't think so.

12:53.270 --> 12:56.630
Okay, I'll talk to you later.

13:01.180 --> 13:02.510
I can't Amelia.

13:02.710 --> 13:04.340
Please, it's my son's wedding.

13:04.850 --> 13:08.510
Just for the day, Lucia.
I'll be back for them tonight.

13:08.620 --> 13:10.850
And what do I say to Mrs. Catherine?

13:11.950 --> 13:15.620
I don't know.
Tell her they're your nephews.

13:15.720 --> 13:17.780
Right, because they look
so much like me...

13:17.890 --> 13:19.860
with my American looking face!

13:21.400 --> 13:22.950
Are we going to see your house?

13:23.060 --> 13:25.930
Yes. You are going to see my house.

13:26.100 --> 13:27.470
Is it far?

13:27.870 --> 13:29.530
No, no.

13:43.120 --> 13:44.350
What's up?

13:45.390 --> 13:46.480
Hi Auntie.

13:46.620 --> 13:48.560
Great to see you, Santiago.

13:51.230 --> 13:52.450
Mike. Debbie.

13:52.690 --> 13:53.720
Hello!

13:54.360 --> 13:55.800
Hello, hello.

13:55.900 --> 13:57.630
They're really shy.

13:57.800 --> 13:59.600
What? These kids
are coming with us?

13:59.700 --> 14:01.900
I couldn't find anyone to watch them.

14:02.140 --> 14:03.830
Their parents won't return tonight.

14:03.940 --> 14:05.840
Why bring them?
They'll drive you crazy.

14:05.940 --> 14:08.140
Don't worry,
they're very good kids.

14:09.040 --> 14:11.480
Don't you want to
leave them with somebody?

14:11.580 --> 14:12.940
I know a girl who
can take care of them.

14:13.050 --> 14:15.850
Are you crazy?
I have to take them with me.

14:15.950 --> 14:17.680
I can't leave them
with just anybody.

14:19.650 --> 14:20.680
Are you sure, Auntie?

14:39.210 --> 14:40.500
You want to order?

14:41.680 --> 14:45.840
Yeah, I'll have the chicken couscous
and a Coke.

14:47.820 --> 14:49.780
What do you have
that doesn't have fat in it?

14:49.880 --> 14:51.180
Everything is delicious.

14:52.490 --> 14:55.420
I'll have the fried eggplant
and a Diet Coke.

14:55.520 --> 14:57.290
Sorry, we don't have Diet Coke.

14:57.390 --> 14:59.760
- Then a regular Coke.
- Two Cokes.

15:16.680 --> 15:18.650
Richard, why did we come here?

15:22.820 --> 15:24.110
What do you mean, why?

15:24.220 --> 15:27.650
Really. Why are we here?

15:33.730 --> 15:35.250
To be alone.

15:39.670 --> 15:40.960
"Alone."

15:53.750 --> 15:55.940
- Throw out the ice.
- The Coke's hot.

15:56.050 --> 15:59.540
Yeah, but you don't know
what kind of water is in there.

16:12.130 --> 16:16.300
Jesus Christ. Why can't you just relax?
Why are you so stressed?

16:16.400 --> 16:20.030
You are the reason I'm stressed.
You're the reason why I can't relax.

16:20.140 --> 16:21.970
You could if you tried.

16:25.710 --> 16:27.680
You don't think I tried?

16:36.460 --> 16:39.050
You're never gonna forgive me,
are you?

16:49.900 --> 16:52.170
You know what I'm talking about.

16:54.310 --> 16:56.280
Hey. I'm not gonna argue.

17:04.720 --> 17:05.950
Okay.

17:08.590 --> 17:11.460
You just let me know
when you're ready to argue.

17:12.990 --> 17:15.460
If you're not gonna run away again.

19:15.980 --> 19:18.580
- Honey? What happened?
- I'm okay.

19:18.690 --> 19:21.310
Honey, what happened?
What happened?

19:22.420 --> 19:24.050
You're bleeding, you're bleeding.

19:25.590 --> 19:27.490
- Oh, my God!
- She's been shot!

19:27.590 --> 19:29.030
Jesus. What happened?

19:29.130 --> 19:31.760
You're bleeding. Oh, my God!

19:33.370 --> 19:35.030
Stop the bus!

19:36.970 --> 19:38.400
- What happened?
- Stop the bus!

20:17.210 --> 20:18.870
The ball was out.

20:23.720 --> 20:24.840
That was out.

20:25.250 --> 20:26.720
No, it was good.

20:26.950 --> 20:27.920
That was out.

20:31.260 --> 20:33.280
I'm deaf, not blind.

20:34.630 --> 20:35.720
You're out.

20:54.880 --> 20:59.950
You shouldn't have lost your temper.
We lost the game.

21:00.390 --> 21:02.790
It wasn't my fault,
it was the ref.

21:04.060 --> 21:08.500
If you hadn't been thrown out,
we would've won the game.

21:11.130 --> 21:13.220
Why are you
in a bad mood?

21:14.570 --> 21:18.370
She's always in a bad mood
because nobody's fucked her yet.

21:19.440 --> 21:22.380
I'm gonna fuck your dad
to get rid of my mood.

21:30.880 --> 21:32.550
I'll see you at the J-Pop.

21:49.870 --> 21:52.340
What do you want to eat?

21:53.970 --> 21:57.270
I said I'd meet my friends
from the team at J-Pop.

21:58.310 --> 22:01.800
Didn't you tell me
we would have lunch together?

22:01.980 --> 22:04.610
Dad, I told you I was
going to eat with them.

22:04.920 --> 22:07.580
You never pay attention to me.

22:17.160 --> 22:20.830
My mother always
paid attention to me.

22:26.040 --> 22:29.600
Why do you want to fight?

22:35.080 --> 22:40.610
I miss your mother too.

22:47.790 --> 22:51.160
I'm doing the best I can.

23:09.050 --> 23:11.920
Don't forget
the dentist at three.

23:17.090 --> 23:18.420
Take care.

23:52.590 --> 23:53.750
Do you have a table?

24:07.240 --> 24:09.440
Why all the way in the corner?

24:12.810 --> 24:14.580
Isn't the view nice?

24:29.800 --> 24:31.700
Do you like him?

25:06.330 --> 25:07.530
Hello.

25:12.640 --> 25:13.800
Hello.

25:19.850 --> 25:21.180
Can I play with you?

25:22.820 --> 25:24.810
Or you can
have a drink with us?

25:27.550 --> 25:29.350
Tell him to speak slowly.

25:29.890 --> 25:32.790
Can you say that
a little slower?

25:47.240 --> 25:49.900
You assholes,
how embarrassing.

26:10.530 --> 26:11.830
What's the matter?

26:13.530 --> 26:16.760
They look at us
like we're monsters.

26:16.870 --> 26:18.600
Oh, come off it.

26:33.620 --> 26:34.880
What are you doing?

26:35.220 --> 26:38.350
Now they're going to meet
the real hairy monster.

27:34.880 --> 27:37.210
<i>Don't forget your appointment
with the dentist. Papa.</i>

27:38.020 --> 27:39.350
I have to go.

27:39.450 --> 27:41.220
I'll see you at your place, then.

28:22.860 --> 28:24.190
What are you doing here?

28:25.030 --> 28:27.060
Something we ate
gave us a stomach ache.

28:27.330 --> 28:29.530
The goats will die
if they don't eat.

28:29.640 --> 28:31.660
Wash your face
and take them out again.

28:31.770 --> 28:33.200
My stomach hurts.

28:33.470 --> 28:35.870
There are other
chores to do then.

28:35.980 --> 28:38.410
Move it. Let's go.

29:09.480 --> 29:11.770
God bless. Bye, bye.

29:14.310 --> 29:16.710
Thank you,
I'll see you tomorrow.

29:19.390 --> 29:21.380
Tell your mother
to prepare dinner.

29:40.310 --> 29:42.210
Did you kill any jackals?

29:42.540 --> 29:45.670
We shot at them,
but didn't hit any.

29:46.150 --> 29:49.410
You have to kill them.
If not, they're going to eat all the goats.

29:49.820 --> 29:51.480
Why did you come home late?

29:52.490 --> 29:55.750
They closed the road,
we took the long way.

29:58.060 --> 30:01.760
Apparently some terrorists
killed an American tourist.

30:02.300 --> 30:03.630
An American?

30:03.860 --> 30:06.490
Yes, the terrorists attacked
a tour bus on the road.

30:07.900 --> 30:10.170
No, there aren't any terrorists here.

30:11.300 --> 30:12.290
You never know.

30:18.140 --> 30:19.940
How do you know
the American died?

30:20.050 --> 30:24.450
That's what they were saying.
The police are looking for the culprits.

31:23.710 --> 31:25.870
You see how easy it is
to get into paradise?

31:25.980 --> 31:27.210
Is this Mexico?

31:27.380 --> 31:29.040
Yes, this is Mexico.

31:29.250 --> 31:32.380
My mom told me
that Mexico is really dangerous.

31:32.590 --> 31:35.350
Yeah... it's full of Mexicans.

31:35.460 --> 31:36.720
Don't talk like that.

31:37.390 --> 31:38.450
It's not true.

31:43.630 --> 31:46.000
I mean, yeah, it's full of Mexicans, but...

33:18.360 --> 33:22.760
How wonderful, you made it.

33:23.630 --> 33:25.500
You decided to bring them?

33:25.730 --> 33:26.960
Hey, what's up?

33:30.470 --> 33:33.700
Oh, son, look how handsome.

33:34.170 --> 33:36.300
You look like Julio Preciado.

33:36.410 --> 33:40.370
Forget Julio Preciado,
he looks like Luis Miguel.

33:43.080 --> 33:44.570
Debbie. Mike.

33:44.680 --> 33:46.710
These are the kids
I take care of.

33:46.820 --> 33:48.310
Say hi to Luis.

33:49.920 --> 33:51.750
Lucio, come here.

33:51.860 --> 33:54.120
This is Mike and Debbie.

33:54.230 --> 33:56.750
He's called Lucio.
He's gonna take care of you, okay?

33:56.860 --> 33:59.060
Take them to play.

34:07.670 --> 34:11.340
Mom, I don't know how you did it,
but it zipped up perfectly.

34:11.440 --> 34:13.670
And it's been 15 years
since I wore this dress.

34:14.150 --> 34:15.980
You haven't changed a bit, Ma.

34:16.080 --> 34:19.420
Working dear, hard work...
that's what keeps you young.

34:21.550 --> 34:22.920
What are you guys laughing about?

34:23.020 --> 34:24.720
Nothing Ma, nothing.

34:40.110 --> 34:43.560
I'll give a buck to the first
who catches a chicken.

34:45.410 --> 34:47.540
Careful with the 'huevos.'

34:56.760 --> 34:58.380
Very good, Debbie got one.

35:01.630 --> 35:02.820
Debbie's the winner.

35:02.930 --> 35:05.090
Okay, now we need another five.

35:05.200 --> 35:07.060
So we have five chickens here.

35:07.470 --> 35:09.400
Okay, now who's going to help me?

35:10.940 --> 35:13.060
You? Okay, come.

35:13.470 --> 35:15.100
Hold it tight, like this.

35:15.680 --> 35:17.010
Grab it right.

35:21.110 --> 35:25.850
Everyone back up...
give me some room.

35:41.970 --> 35:43.530
Someone, help!

35:59.420 --> 36:01.650
Is anybody a doctor? Please, a doctor!

36:08.060 --> 36:11.390
- Where's the nearest hospital?
- It's far away. About four hours.

36:11.500 --> 36:13.490
- Is there anything closer?
- There's a clinic.

36:13.600 --> 36:16.800
But on the south. In the bus
it will take us an hour and a half.

36:16.900 --> 36:20.600
- Away from Ouarzazate?
- Yes. It's the closest thing we've got.

36:22.740 --> 36:24.370
Get down!

36:24.940 --> 36:26.740
- Put that there.
- Okay.

36:30.180 --> 36:33.020
Stop! Stop!

36:34.790 --> 36:36.910
We need your help.
My wife's been injured.

36:37.620 --> 36:40.790
I need your help. Help. Hospital.

36:40.890 --> 36:42.720
Help, come here.
Tell him we need his help!

36:42.830 --> 36:47.430
No, wait! Wait! Wait!
Stop him! Stop him!

37:01.210 --> 37:03.980
Ouarzazate isn't this way.
They're going to start shooting at us.

37:04.080 --> 37:06.310
- Turn the bus around, Anwar!
- It hurts.

37:06.420 --> 37:08.980
- Turn back. Turn the bus around!
- It really hurts.

37:10.890 --> 37:14.520
We got to get somewhere closer.
Is there anywhere else we can take her?

37:14.630 --> 37:16.090
We can take her to my town.

37:16.200 --> 37:19.960
It's near here, and there is a doctor.
We can call Erfoud for an ambulance.

37:21.770 --> 37:23.200
Okay. Okay.

39:08.540 --> 39:10.370
Watch her shoulder!
Watch her shoulder!

39:10.480 --> 39:11.530
Okay. Okay.

39:15.580 --> 39:18.180
- Turn this way.
- No, no.

39:18.280 --> 39:19.950
Through the next door. Come on.

39:35.430 --> 39:37.770
We got to call an ambulance.
I need to call my embassy.

39:37.870 --> 39:40.270
Okay. If you have the number
of your embassy, I can go call.

39:40.370 --> 39:41.500
Where are you going?

39:41.610 --> 39:43.540
I'll make the call.
Okay, I got to go make a call.

39:43.640 --> 39:45.630
- Please don't leave me here alone.
- You're going to be all right.

39:45.750 --> 39:46.730
- Can she help?
- Yeah, yeah.

39:46.850 --> 39:48.280
Where are you going? Please
don't leave me here alone.

39:48.380 --> 39:49.470
- Can she help?
- Yes.

39:49.580 --> 39:51.910
Listen, listen. It's gonna be all right.
I'm just gonna go make a call.

39:52.020 --> 39:54.920
Wait, wait, wait, wait. Tell her
she has to keep pressure right here.

39:55.020 --> 39:56.610
She cannot let go.
Does she understand?

39:56.720 --> 39:57.710
Yes.

39:57.820 --> 39:59.760
I'm just gonna make sure help's
on the way. I'm coming right back.

39:59.860 --> 40:01.990
- Please don't leave me.
- Does she understand?

40:02.090 --> 40:03.860
- I'll be right back.
- Richard, no, don't leave me here.

40:03.960 --> 40:06.800
- I'll be right back.
- Richard, don't. Richard!

40:06.900 --> 40:09.770
I'll be back, sweetheart.
Just gonna make the call.

40:11.670 --> 40:14.370
- How's your wife?
- It's bad. I can't stop the bleeding.

40:14.470 --> 40:16.870
- Get her out of there and let's go.
- Where? Where do I take her?

40:16.980 --> 40:19.810
In Egypt in a town like this
they slit 30 German tourists' throats.

40:19.910 --> 40:21.240
- They might do the same to us.
- No, sir, not here.

40:21.350 --> 40:23.510
What do you know? We've got to get
